Taliban , Greek Company Sign Accord on Oil , Gas
ISLAMABAD , November 15 ( Xinhua ) -- The Afghan Taliban militia have signed an agreement with a Greek company on oil and gas exploration in Afghanistan , Bakhtar News Agency reported Sunday .
A Taliban official responsible for mines and industries Ahmed Jan is reported to have signed the agreement with the Greek company , CCC , after four days of negotiations .
Under the agreement , the CCC company would soon start oil and gas exploration in Afghanistan 's Herat province .
Recently , a delegation from the U.S. , European countries and South Africa also visited the war-ravaged country to explore the possibilities of investment in different fields , particularly in the fields of communication , mines and oil and gas .
